/*
 * /html-video/ — sister-project landing page for nexu-io/html-video.
 *
 * html-video is the "motion" counterpart of HTML Anything: an HTML→Video
 * meta-layer. A local coding agent turns a prompt, an article link, or a
 * GitHub repo into a multi-frame animated video, then renders a real MP4 on
 * your machine (headless Chromium + ffmpeg). Pluggable engines (Hyperframes
 * shipped; Remotion / Motion Canvas / Manim on the roadmap), 21 templates,
 * optional AI soundtrack. Apache-2.0, local, no per-render fee.
 *
 * SEO surface: the page leads with the two primary head terms — "HTML to
 * video" (the category) and "Hyperframes" (the default engine, a real query
 * for heygen-com/hyperframes) — and seeds long-tail like "html to mp4" and
 * "agent video" through the section copy. Same hardcoded-from-README content
 * model as the HTML Anything page (a separate repo, not a content collection).
 *
 * Content is hardcoded EN + ZH; the other 16 locales derive a keyword-stacked
 * fallback from shared i18n fragments (same pattern as HTML Anything).
 */
